### 13. Call seed in Program.cs

In server Program.cs, AFTER `var app = builder.Build();` add:
```csharp
using (var scope = app.Services.CreateScope())
{
    var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<ApplicationDbContext>();
    db.Database.Migrate();
    SeedData.Initialize(db);
}
```

Wait — for development, use `EnsureCreated()` instead of `Migrate()` since we haven't created migrations:
```csharp
using (var scope = app.Services.CreateScope())
{
    var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<ApplicationDbContext>();
    db.Database.EnsureCreated();
    SeedData.Initialize(db);
}
```

### 14. HttpClient cookie forwarding

For the WebAssembly HttpClient to work with cookie auth, the requests go to the same origin so cookies are sent automatically. No special configuration needed.

### Important notes:
- The server project already references the client project (template does this).
- Make sure the `_Imports.razor` in the client project doesn't need extra usings. It should be fine.
- Do NOT add `@rendermode` to any pages - global mode handles this.

